no edge). Reject extremes 0-15% & 85-100% (distorted pricing). Rationale: Extreme ratios have unrealistic implied probabilities; middle range reflects consensus (no inefficiency). Output: filtered market list for Phase 2. **PHASE 2: LLM-Based Clustering (Daily Scan).** Use LLM embeddings to identify hidden market correlations. Group similar markets (e.g., Bitcoin $100k + Ethereum $5k + Crypto dominance all cluster together). Find markets with strong semantic/causal links that traditional screening misses. Output: market clusters for Phase 3. **PHASE 3: Pearson Pairwise Correlation Detection (Daily Scan).** Apply Pearson/distance-based algorithm (ref: hudson-and-thames-arbitragelab) to detect strongly correlated market pairs. Identify mispricings: if BTC moves +5% in backtest but only +2% in live, that's arbitrage. Calculate expected spread from historical correlation. Score confidence. Output: correlation_pairs.json with arbitrage candidates. **PHASE 4: C++ High-Frequency Execution (Real-Time).** Why C++: Each trade moves prices; we need sub-millisecond execution to capture arbitrage before it reverts. Algorithm: (1) Detect spread gap between correlated markets, (2) Calculate theoretical fair spread, (3) Execute buy/sell pairs to lock profit, (4) Monitor until convergence. No Python delays. No GIL. Pure performance. **Why This Works:** Phases 1-3 reduce noise (99% of markets ignored), find real edges via correlation-based pairs (harder to game than single-market signals), Phase 4 captures spread before reversion. This is the real edge. Reference: https://hudson-and-thames-arbitragelab.readthedocs-hosted.com/en/latest/distance_approach/pearson_approach.html | high | all | undefined | open | 2026-04-03 | 2026-04-03 | Wen Zhou strategy — full 4-phase pipeline. Phases 1-3 = daily batch. Phase 4 = real-time. Blocks live trading pending T236 (API credentials). |\n\n## Instructions (Persistent Context - Always Consider)\n| ID | Title | Description | Priority | Group | Assi